# Styling — Tailwind CSS & shadcn/ui

## Brand Colours (be.brussels)

These are the only approved colours for the application shell. Define them as custom Tailwind
tokens in `tailwind.config.ts` — **never hardcode hex values inline** in component files.

| Role | Hex | Tailwind token (example) |
|---|---|---|
| Sidebar background | `#1a2f4e` | `bg-sidebar` |
| Primary / interactive | `#185FA5` | `bg-primary` |
| Page background | `#f4f6f8` | `bg-surface` |

## Component Library

- Use **shadcn/ui** for all form controls, dialogs, comboboxes (cmdk), and data tables.
- Do **not** mix raw HTML `<input>`, `<select>`, or `<button>` elements with shadcn inputs
  in the same form.
- Use **semantic HTML elements** wherever possible (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`).
- **No inline styles** (`style={{}}`).
- **No global CSS imports** inside component files — Tailwind utility classes only.

## Table Column Headers

Budget, assignment, and EOTP tables must always use these exact column labels — no variations:

```
Internal | External | Direct | Total
```

## Monetary Display

- All monetary values in tables use the **`€k` abbreviation** via the shared `formatK` helper.
- Apply `formatK` consistently across initiative, assignment, and EOTP tables.
- Do not format currency inline with `toLocaleString` or custom logic.

## Images and Fonts

- Use `next/image` for all images — automatic lazy loading and optimisation.
- Use `next/font` to load fonts — prevents layout shift (CLS).

## Performance

- Use `React.memo` to prevent unnecessary re-renders of expensive table rows or cards.
- Minimise state updates — only call `setState` when the value actually changes.
- Clean up event listeners and timers in `useEffect` return functions.
